{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Infrared",
  "description": "Thermal-vision palette mapping, decomposed: ten node.gradient_ramp atoms bake the ten palettes as gradient LUTs, a dynamic node.mux_texture (num_inputs=10) selects the active one from the `palette` knob, and node.color_lut samples it by BT.601 luminance (with contrast) and crossfades against the source. Replaces the fused node.infrared kernel. Nine palettes are bit-exact (the legacy bake IS a piecewise-linear gradient with last-segment extrapolation over luma [0,2], reproduced by gradient_ramp domain=2). Rainbow is procedural in the legacy (a fract triangle-wave); here it's a clean single-cycle hue ramp (domain=1) — visually a rainbow, not the legacy double-cycle.",
